SourceTree version: 3.3.8

Windows version: windows 10 Home - 18363.720

 

Sourcetree is setting a config in C:\Users\<name>\.gitconfig which looks like

 

{{}}
{code:java}
[credential "helperselector"]
         selected = manager
{code}
This is causing problem with git version 2.26.2 by giving warning and in github desktop unable to push by giving error 

{{}}
{code:java}
warning: url has no scheme: helperselector
fatal: credential url cannot be parsed: helperselector{code}
 

{{}}

{{}}

Windows is case insensitive and so when renaming a branch's capitalisation, an error will occur (branch already exists).

SRCTREE-713 implemented ability to rename branch.

BCLOUD-11637 was closed but I think an opportunity was missed to improve sourcetree.

It would be useful to add an option to force rename in Sourcetree, ie perform:
{code:java}
git branch -M newName{code}
